# Registry Hives

There are five major Registry hives every administrator should know.

---

# 1. HKLM (HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE)

Most important hive.

Stores **computer-wide settings**.

Contains:

* Installed software
* Drivers
* Services
* Hardware
* Security
* Boot configuration

Example:

```text
HKLM
```

---

### Important Paths

## HKLM\Software

Stores:

* Installed applications
* Microsoft products
* Application settings

Example:

```text
HKLM\Software\Microsoft
```

PowerShell

```powershell
Get-Item HKLM:\Software
```

---

## HKLM\System

Stores:

* Drivers
* Services
* Boot configuration
* Hardware profile

Example:

```text
HKLM\System
```

---

## HKLM\Security

Stores:

* Local security policy
* Security descriptors

Highly protected.

Even administrators cannot normally read it directly.

---

## HKLM\SAM

Stores:

* Local user accounts
* Local password hashes

Very sensitive.

Protected by Windows.

---

## HKLM\CurrentControlSet\Services

One of the most important Registry locations.

Contains configuration for every Windows service.

Example:

```text
HKLM
  └── CurrentControlSet
          └── Services
```

Inside:

```text
Spooler

DHCP

WinRM

LanmanServer

EventLog
```

Each service has:

* Startup Type
* ImagePath
* Dependencies
* Service Account
* Failure actions

PowerShell

```powershell
Get-ChildItem HKLM:\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services
```

---

# 2. HKCU (HKEY_CURRENT_USER)

Stores settings for the currently logged-in user.

Contains:

* Desktop settings
* Wallpapers
* Printers
* Mouse
* Keyboard
* Office settings
* User preferences

Example:

```text
HKCU\Software
```

PowerShell

```powershell
Get-ChildItem HKCU:\Software
```

---

# 3. HKCR (HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT)

Stores:

* File associations
* COM registrations
* Shell extensions

Example:

```text
.txt

.docx

.pdf
```

Determines which application opens a file.

---

# 4. HKU (HKEY_USERS)

Contains profiles for all users loaded on the computer.

Example:

```text
HKU
 ├── Default
 ├── S-1-5-18
 ├── S-1-5-19
 └── User SID
```

Every logged-in user has a Registry profile here.

---

# 5. HKCC (HKEY_CURRENT_CONFIG)

Stores:

Current hardware profile.

Contains:

* Display
* Printer
* Current hardware configuration

---

# Registry Hives Summary

| Hive | Purpose                  |
| ---- | ------------------------ |
| HKLM | Computer settings        |
| HKCU | Current user settings    |
| HKCR | File associations        |
| HKU  | All user profiles        |
| HKCC | Current hardware profile |

