# PowerShell Registry Health Check Tool

```powershell
Write-Host "========== REGISTRY HEALTH CHECK ==========" -ForegroundColor Cyan

Write-Host "`nInstalled Software Key" -ForegroundColor Yellow
Test-Path "HKLM:\SOFTWARE"

Write-Host "`nCurrent User Software Key" -ForegroundColor Yellow
Test-Path "HKCU:\SOFTWARE"

Write-Host "`nService Registry Keys (Top 10)" -ForegroundColor Yellow
Get-ChildItem "HKLM:\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services" |
Select-Object -First 10 Name

Write-Host "`nWindows Current Version Information" -ForegroundColor Yellow
Get-ItemProperty "HKLM:\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion" |
Select-Object ProductName, CurrentBuild, DisplayVersion

Write-Host "`nRegistry Health Check Completed." -ForegroundColor Green
```

